answers.answer: I have pains in my ribs but it comes and goes, its just my baby wedging himself in there. Does Tylenol help you? Or sitting straight up?

That could be a sign of preeclampsia.  If Tylenol doesn't help, you have excessive swelling, headache that doesn't go away with Tylenol, and high blood pressure? Not trying to freak you out but keep it in mind. Good luck.

I don't take Tylenol...and its not constant, only when I check my blind spot while driving, or turn over in bed. Sometimes my doctor put her feet here but she doesn't wedge herself near my ribs (thank god)  my blood pressure has always been phenomenal, just some mild swelling some days and no complaints of headaches.

question: I've had a slight dull pain on my right side, right at the bottom indentation of my rib cage. I thought it was maybe a pulled muscle/ligament but its been over a week and it feels almost like an eternal bruise :/  I have a doctors appointment Tuesday and I'll tell my ob I was just curious if anyone else has had this. I'm a ftm, 34 weeks on tuesday
title: anyone else?
